<paragraph id="85233320FF83FF92AF9640A272C3523E" blockId="5.[677,1216,1490,1699]" lastBlockId="6.[112,648,215,583]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="261" pageId="5" pageNumber="260">
DIAGNOSE. — 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF83FF91AE7540A270955593" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1872" box="[838,986,1490,1514]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="5" pageNumber="260" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mylodontinae">Mylodontinae</taxonomicName>
de petite taille (voir 
<tableCitation id="C81E069BFF83FF91AF96409C71B0567D" box="[677,767,1516,1540]" captionStart="TABLEAU" captionStartId="5.[114,122,219,236]" captionText="TABLEAU 1. — Principales dimensions (en mm) du crâne holotype de Pleurolestodon dalenzae n. sp. (MNHN-BOL V 3348)." pageId="5" pageNumber="260">Tableau 1</tableCitation>
), plus petit que 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF83FF91AEAB409C702B5666" authority="(Kraglievich, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Kraglievich" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Glossotheridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="5" pageNumber="260" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chapadmalense">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF83FF91AEAB409C77F5567D" box="[920,1210,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="260">Glossotheridium chapadmalense</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF83FF91AF98437770125666" author="KRAGLIEVICH L." box="[683,861,1543,1567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="260" pagination="215 - 235" refId="ref31275" refString="KRAGLIEVICH L. 1925. - Cuatro nuevos gravigrados de la fauna araucana &quot; chapadmalense &quot;. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 33: 215 - 235." type="journal article" year="1925">Kraglievich, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
mais plus grand que 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF83FF91A908437670C15640" authority="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe, 2010" authorityName="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe" authorityYear="2010" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Simomylodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="5" pageNumber="272" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uccasamamensis" status="n. gen.,">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF83FF91A908437670725640" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="260">Simomylodon uccasamamensis</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ACDB5249FF83FF91AE76435170C15640" box="[837,910,1569,1593]" pageId="5" pageNumber="260" rank="species">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
, n. sp.; séries dentaires fortement divergentes (cependant moins que chez le genre Quaternaire 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF83FF91AE17432670E55617" authorityName="Owen" authorityYear="1839" box="[804,938,1622,1646]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Glossotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="5" pageNumber="260" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF83FF91AE17432670E55617" box="[804,938,1622,1646]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="260">Glossotherium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dépourvues de diastème; le rapport de la distance entre les faces internes des C d’une part, et celle entre les faces internes des M4 d’autre part, varie entre 1,61 (
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AC7D45A872F35096" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[334,444,215,239]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AC7D45A872F35096" box="[334,444,215,239]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) et 2,21 (
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AF2D45A871C95096" authority="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe, 2010" authorityName="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe" authorityYear="2010" box="[542,646,215,239]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dalenzae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AF2D45A871C95096" box="[542,646,215,239]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. dalenzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ACDB5249FF80FF92AD41458173E45170" box="[114,171,241,265]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); la base antérieure de l’arcade zygomatique se situe sur les parois latérales du maxillaire à un niveau situé entre le milieu de la M2 et l’extrémité postérieure de la M3 (comme chez 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AC69443171595120" authorityName="Hoffstetter" authorityYear="1961" box="[346,534,321,345]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pseudoprepotherium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AC69443171595120" box="[346,534,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pseudoprepotherium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), la section de la M2 est allongée antéropostérieurement, en forme de triangle rectangle d’angle droit antérolingual, avec sillon lingual large et profond et face postérolabiale très longue; l’extrémité postérieure du palais est nettement en arrière du plan transversal passant par les processus post-orbitaires; les nasaux s’immisçant en pointe dans le bord antérieur des frontaux; présence d’un petit élément internasal pair se projetant vers l’avant à l’extrémité médio-antérieure des nasaux.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85233320FF80FF92AD42470473A652F5" blockId="6.[110,649,628,1700]" box="[113,233,628,654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">REMARQUE</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85233320FF80FF92AD4247E37154567F" blockId="6.[110,649,628,1700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">
Le genre 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92ADEB47E3722252D4" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[216,365,659,685]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92ADEB47E3722252D4" box="[216,365,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a été défini par 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AF1547E373F252B7" author="ROVERETO C." pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto (1914)</bibRefCitation>
sur la base de matériel provenant du Huayquérien (Miocène supérieur) de la 
<collectingRegion id="4758FDC2FF80FF92ACE347A373FD5374" country="Argentina" name="Catamarca" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Province de Catamarca</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="FD8B73B0FF80FF92ADF34782727E5374" box="[192,305,754,781]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Argentine</collectingCountry>
). Initialement, 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92ACE6478271C95374" author="ROVERETO C." box="[469,646,754,781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto (1914)</bibRefCitation>
définit trois espèces constituant le genre 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AF0A4662738E5335" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AF0A4662738E5335" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92ADE3464372875334" authority="Rovereto, 1914" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[208,456,818,845]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="avitus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92ADE34643726D5335" box="[208,290,819,844]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P.avitus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AC14464272875334" author="ROVERETO C." box="[295,456,818,845]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(spécimens types: MACN-Pv 2785 et 2952), 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92ACAF462273E853F5" authority="Rovereto, 1914" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92ACAF4622715A5312" box="[412,533,849,875]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AF2E462173E853F5" author="ROVERETO C." pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(spécimen type: MACN-Pv 2953) et 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AF184602720553D5" authority="Rovereto, 1914" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrodon">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AF18460273D753D2" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. macrodon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AD9246E1720553D5" author="ROVERETO C." box="[161,330,913,940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(spécimen type: MACN-Pv 2784). 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92ADF146C072C253B2" author="KRAGLIEVICH L." box="[194,397,944,971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="95 - 118" refId="ref31199" refString="KRAGLIEVICH L. 1921. - Estudios sobre los Mylodontinae. Descripcion comparativa del genero &quot; Pleurolestodon &quot; Rov. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 31: 95 - 118." type="journal article" year="1921">Kraglievich (1921)</bibRefCitation>
effectuant une révision du matériel décrit préalablement par Rovereto et déposé au MACN de 
<collectingRegion id="4758FDC2FF80FF92AC5E4680714C5472" box="[365,515,1008,1035]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
, estime que 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AD40416073BD5450" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[115,242,1039,1065]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrodon">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AD40416073BD5450" box="[115,242,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. macrodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est synonyme de 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AC80416071645450" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[435,555,1039,1065]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AC80416071645450" box="[435,555,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. En cela nous suivons l’opinion présentée par 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AF3F415F73F25413" author="KRAGLIEVICH L." pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="95 - 118" refId="ref31199" refString="KRAGLIEVICH L. 1921. - Estudios sobre los Mylodontinae. Descripcion comparativa del genero &quot; Pleurolestodon &quot; Rov. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 31: 95 - 118." type="journal article" year="1921">Kraglievich (1921)</bibRefCitation>
. De plus comme le signalait 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92ACE9413F71CB5413" author="ROVERETO C." box="[474,644,1103,1130]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto (1914)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AD5C411F738B54F1" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[111,196,1135,1160]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="avitus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AD5C411F738B54F1" box="[111,196,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. avitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
présente de très nombreuses affinités avec 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AD4141FF73B954D1" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[114,246,1166,1192]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrodon">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AD4141FF73B954D1" box="[114,246,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. macrodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et les seules différences « notables » présentées par 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AC2741DE728254B0" author="ROVERETO C." box="[276,461,1198,1225]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto (1914)</bibRefCitation>
, principalement dentaires, ne nous semblent pas suffisantes pour définir deux espèces de 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AC45419D7144557E" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[374,523,1261,1287]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AC45419D7144557E" box="[374,523,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
au sein du matériel provenant de 
<collectingRegion id="4758FDC2FF80FF92AC6A407D72825551" box="[345,461,1293,1320]" country="Argentina" name="Catamarca" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Catamarca</collectingRegion>
.Pour cette raison, nous considérions jusqu’à la réalisation du présent manuscrit, 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92ADDA403C7233551F" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[233,380,1356,1382]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92ADDA403C7233551F" box="[233,380,1356,1382]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comme monospécifique. 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AD41401C722C55FF" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[114,355,1388,1414]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AD41401C722C55FF" box="[114,355,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est l’unique espèce valide du Huayquérien de 
<collectingRegion id="4758FDC2FF80FF92AC1740FC72D355DE" box="[292,412,1420,1447]" country="Argentina" name="Catamarca" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Catamarca</collectingRegion>
. L’holotype de 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AF0C40FC73E255BC" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AF0C40FC73E255BC" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est le spécimen MACN-Pv 2953 alors que les spécimens MACN-Pv 2784, 2785 et 2952 sont désormais considérés comme 
<typeStatus id="5A278D82FF80FF92AC9D409B7158567F" box="[430,535,1515,1542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85233320FF80FF92ADBB437A710356DD" blockId="6.[110,649,628,1700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">
Les deux espèces qui composent ainsi le genre 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AD40435A7248563D" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[115,263,1578,1604]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AD40435A7248563D" box="[115,263,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proviennent du Miocène supérieur (Huayquérien-Montehermoséen) d’Argentine (Province de Catamarca – 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AC5F431A72A756FA" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[364,488,1641,1667]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AC5F431A72A756FA" box="[364,488,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) et de 
<collectingCountry id="FD8B73B0FF80FF92AF09431971C956FD" box="[570,646,1641,1668]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Bolivie</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4758FDC2FF80FF92AD4843F9722356DD" box="[123,364,1673,1700]" country="Bolivia" name="Oruro" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Département d’Oruro</collectingRegion>
– 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92ACBB43FA72B456DA" authority="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe, 2010" authorityName="Saint-André &amp; Pujos &amp; Cartelle &amp; De Iuliis &amp; Gaudin &amp; McDonald &amp; Mamani Quispe" authorityYear="2010" box="[392,507,1673,1699]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dalenzae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92ACBB43FA72B456DA" box="[392,507,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. dalenzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ACDB5249FF80FF92AF3143F9717056DD" box="[514,575,1673,1700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85233320FF80FF92AF8845A8772A51A8" blockId="6.[677,1212,216,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">
Une révision récente par A. Kramarz du matériel attribué à 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AE09458770815168" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[826,974,247,273]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AE09458770815168" box="[826,974,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">Pleurolestodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et déposé au MACN, a permis de noter l’absence du spécimen 
<typeStatus id="5A278D82FF80FF92A95A446777D8514B" box="[1129,1175,279,306]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">type</typeStatus>
de 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AF954448706D5128" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[678,802,311,337]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AF954448706D5128" box="[678,802,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MACN-Pv 2953, A. Kramarz pers. comm. 2008). Cependant la description détaillée et les excellentes illustrations présentes dans la publication de 
<bibRefCitation id="E10D4ED1FF80FF92AE7E44E6774F51C8" author="ROVERETO C." box="[845,1024,406,433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref32334" refString="ROVERETO C. 1914. - Los estratos Araucanos y sus fosiles. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Buenos Aires 25: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="1914">Rovereto (1914)</bibRefCitation>
nous ont permis d’utiliser le spécimen 
<typeStatus id="5A278D82FF80FF92AEA344C670F151A8" box="[912,958,438,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">type</typeStatus>
de 
<taxonomicName id="429C48A3FF80FF92AED644C6771151B6" authorityName="Rovereto" authorityYear="1914" box="[997,1118,437,463]" class="Mammalia" family="Mylodontidae" genus="Pleurolestodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pilosa" pageId="6" pageNumber="261" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis id="B7E8EF32FF80FF92AED644C6771151B6" box="[997,1118,437,463]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="261">P. acutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
